ETF of ETF Project - TW market Percentage Portfolio Sensitive Analysis

This project aims to develop the index series for Taiwanese investors who seeking global asset allocation and finds out what is the optimal percentage of exposure at Taiwan market. Each index is composed of ETFs. The index series is comprised of four indices, each one measuring the performance of specific allocations to equities and fixed income. The indices represent stock-bond allocations across a risk spectrum from conservative to aggressive.

def ln_return(series):
    #calculate natural log return
    ln_rts = lambda y,x: (y-x)/x
    series = ln_rts(series,series.shift(1))
    return series

Plotting the Stats

def plot_ratio_stats(x):
    plt.figure(figsize=(21, 8))  # make separate figure
    ax = plt.subplot(1, 1, 1)
    new_ticks = np.linspace(0., 1, 20)
    plt.xticks(new_ticks)
    
    a= df.iloc[x,:]
    b= df1.iloc[x,:]
    c= df2.iloc[x,:]
    d= df3.iloc[x,:]
    
    max_indx1=np.argmax(a)#max value index
    min_indx1=np.argmin(a)#min value index
    max_indx2=np.argmax(b)#max value index
    min_indx2=np.argmin(b)#min value index
    max_indx3=np.argmax(c)#max value index
    min_indx3=np.argmin(c)#min value index
    max_indx4=np.argmax(d)#max value index
    min_indx4=np.argmin(d)#min value index
    
    plt.plot(a, label= '37')
    plt.plot(b, label= '46')
    plt.plot(c, label= '64')
    plt.plot(d, label= '82')

    plt.plot(max_indx1,a[max_indx1],'b*')
    show_max1='['+str(max_indx1)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_max1,xytext=(max_indx1,a[max_indx1]),xy=(max_indx1,a[max_indx1]))
    plt.plot(min_indx1,a[min_indx1],'b*')   
    show_min1='['+str(min_indx1)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_min1,xytext=(min_indx1,a[min_indx1]),xy=(min_indx1,a[min_indx1]))
    
    plt.plot(max_indx2,b[max_indx2],'y*')
    show_max2='['+str(max_indx2)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_max2,xytext=(max_indx2,b[max_indx2]),xy=(max_indx2,b[max_indx2]))
    plt.plot(min_indx2,b[min_indx2],'y*')   
    show_min2='['+str(min_indx2)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_min2,xytext=(min_indx2,b[min_indx2]),xy=(min_indx2,b[min_indx2]))
    
    plt.plot(max_indx3,c[max_indx3],'g*')
    show_max3='['+str(max_indx3)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_max3,xytext=(max_indx3,c[max_indx3]),xy=(max_indx3,c[max_indx3]))
    plt.plot(min_indx3,c[min_indx3],'g*')   
    show_min3='['+str(min_indx3)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_min3,xytext=(min_indx3,c[min_indx3]),xy=(min_indx3,c[min_indx3]))
    
    plt.plot(max_indx4,d[max_indx4],'r*')
    show_max4='['+str(max_indx4)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_max4,xytext=(max_indx4,d[max_indx4]),xy=(max_indx4,d[max_indx4]))
    plt.plot(min_indx4,d[min_indx4],'r*')   
    show_min4='['+str(min_indx4)+']'
    plt.annotate(show_min4,xytext=(min_indx4,d[min_indx4]),xy=(min_indx4,d[min_indx4]))

    plt.title(df.index[x])
    plt.grid(True,axis='both')
    # plt.ylabel('Cumulative Returns (%)')
    plt.legend(['37','46','64','82'])
    plt.show
    
for i in range(len(df)):
    plot_ratio_stats(i)
